  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study is to demonstrate that the MDT-2211 renal denervation system is a
      safe and effective treatment for uncontrolled hypertension subjects despite treatment with 3
      or more anti-hypertensive medications of different classes, of which one must be a diuretic,
      as best available antihypertensive therapy
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The HTN-J study is a multi-center, prospective, unblinded, randomized, controlled study of
      the safety and effectiveness of renal denervation in subjects with uncontrolled hypertension.
      Bilateral renal denervation will be performed using the MDT-2211 renal denervation system - a
      percutaneous system that delivers radiofrequency (RF) energy through the luminal surface of
      the renal artery.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
